shapes3d.path

Class Lissajous

  • java.lang.Object
    • shapes3d.path.AbstractPath
      • shapes3d.path.Lissajous
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    processing.core.PConstants, Path, SConstants

    public final class Lissajous
extends AbstractPath
    A path through 3D space based on the Lissajous curve.
    It is unlikely that you would want to use this path except for demonstration purposes.
    Author:
    Peter Lager

    • Constructor Detail

      • Lissajous

        public Lissajous(int nbrSlices)
        Define the detail level for a Lissajous curve with coefficients 1, 3, 5.
        Best result comes from using a large number of slices.
        Parameters:
        nbrSlices - number of slices along the path length

      • Lissajous

        public Lissajous(int xCoef,
                 int yCoef,
                 int zCoef,
                 int nbrSlices)
        Define the 3 Lissajous coefficients and detail level.
        Best result comes from using small prime numbers for the coefficients, also using a large number of slices.
        Parameters:
        xCoef - x coefficient
        yCoef - y coefficient
        zCoef - z coefficient
        nbrSlices - number of slices along the path length

      • Lissajous

        public Lissajous(int xCoef,

                 int zCoef,
                 int nbrSlices,
                 PathOrthogonal ortho)
        Define the 3 Lissajous coefficients, detail level and othogonal calculator.
        Best result comes from using small prime numbers for the coefficients, also using a large number of slices.
        Parameters:
        xCoef - x coefficient
        yCoef - y coefficient
        zCoef - z coefficient
        nbrSlices - number of slices along the path length
        ortho - the orthogonal calculator to use
